    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - ADJUSTMENTS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ADJUSTMENTS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="align" graphiccount="1">
            <title>CAB TO CHASSIS ALIGNMENT</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set chassis on a level surface.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure cab hinge pivot bolts are tightened to 210 to 230 ft-lbs. (285 to 312 Nm). To
                    tighten the cab hinge pivot bolt, it will be necessary to remove the lower section of the grille.
                    Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16018_27.xml" xrefid="hl1601821">GRILLE ASSEMBLY, Remove
                        <xref refid="hl1601821"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check cab alignment with chassis frame (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601892">Figure 92</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601892" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601892" filename="../figg16/G1601892.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 92. Check Cab Alignment</caption>
                </figure>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If cab is not square with chassis, make a complete cab adjustment. Refer to
                        <hotlnk document="s16018_48.xml" xrefid="hl1601822">CAB FRONT AND REAR MOUNT ADJUSTMENT
                            <xref refid="hl1601822"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If cab alignment is OK but cab does not seat properly in latches, adjust at cab rear
                        mounts only. Refer to
                        <hotlnk document="s16018_48.xml" xrefid="hl1601822">CAB FRONT AND REAR MOUNT ADJUSTMENT
                            <xref refid="hl1601822"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
